cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of the interactive proof assistant Isabelle/HOL for mathematical analysis and verification of probabilistic systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with the verification of distributed protocols. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as one of the case studies involves the verification of anonymity properties of a protocol. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with the verification of Markov chains, which are a fundamental data structure in probabilistic modeling. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of formal methods for software verification.
